>>13242764
Something about the first person present tense and the diction seems really off. There's also a level of superfluous detail that feels really weird to read. Take this:
>”I just wanted to ask you if you wanted to meet up.” she says straightly and I swallow the singular grape in my mouth
You didn't need to use "singular" or "in my mouth" there for the reader to get the exact same thing out of the line. Also look at something like this:
>I open the garage door with the button on the wall and press another button to stop its ascent after reaching a height for the car to pass through
>After glancing at the afternoon sky, I get into the car and start it up, it’s engine purring nicely as I drive it out and then lower the door with the remote I took out of the glove box
This could have been distilled to
>I open the garage door, and after glancing at the afternoon sky, I get into the car and start it up, its engine purring nicely as I drive it out
So basically just level out the detail to something more manageable and not overloading and also make the narration flow a bit better with some better word choice and you'll have something really good.
